history.content:
They are both useful classes. It just depends on what you are more interested in. 186 only covers databases which can be useful for SWE, whereas Data 100 covers a lot of data science topics, but not in depth. Although data100 is not very in depth...it is a really important class for DS. 

________

However, don't go into 186 thinking it's a low-workload class. I'm spending much more time on it than on 188, and it's almost the same amount of time I spend on 170 (comparable because I'm taking these 3 courses together lol)

________

Yeah Data 100 (Spring 19) was much less stressful than 186 has been for me; definitely a medium+ workload class with annoying, ambiguously worded projects (which are apparently intended to be so in order to emulate the "real world"TM experience)
